:"valcarenghi: pic#125911873","article":"It's a great anthology, as is Old Mars. I hope you and Gardner will continue to explore the Solar System, planet by planet, once his ankle is mended and that pesky simian (Kong) is done and dusted.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"10 months ago","ctime":"July 2 2016, 22:13:53 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Congratulations!","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://valcarenghi.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"valcarenghi","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"valcarenghi","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://valcarenghi.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"valcarenghi","ctime_ts":1467497633,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/110839817/38438372","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/491941.html?replyto=24726693","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/491941.html?thread=24726693#t24726693","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/491941.html?thread=24726693#t24726693","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/491941.html?thread=24726693#t24726693","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"robski2010","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://robski2010.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":24726693,"talkid":96588,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/491941.html?thread=24726693#t24726693","upictitle":"Robert Mathison: pic#110839817","article":"Hi Mr. Martin have a quick question about your writing style.  It's no secret you have written/edited massive length books from A Song of Ice and Fire, to the Wild Card franchise and of course to Old Venus.  But one thing that I noticed when reading the series is how much of a page turner these books are, despite at times being near or above 1,000 pages these books are amazing and keep me engaged and wanting to get to the next chapter.  My question is when you first started writing/editing a series were you afraid the length of the books were too long for audiences to read without it dragging compared to a 300 page book?  Again thanks for reading this and you are fantastic author and human being!","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"10 months ago","ctime":"July 3 2016, 01:48:24 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://robski2010.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"robski2010","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"robski2010","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://robski2010.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"robski2010","ctime_ts":1467510504,"tracked":0}]}